description: Air India, now under Tata Group, continues to face issues with clogged toilets caused by passengers flushing inappropriate items. title: Meet Roshni Nadar, HCL founder's daughter, who is now India's richest woman

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi received a warm welcome in Mauritius, marked by a traditional Geet Gawai performance. During his visit, Modi will participate in National Day celebrations and inaugurate various India-funded projects, highlighting bilateral ties and mutual cooperation between India and Mauritius.
title: Watch: PM Modi receives traditional Bihari welcome in Mauritius

description: A US judge halted the deportation of Palestinian student Mahmoud Khalil, detained by immigration officials executing a State Department directive to cancel his green card. Khalil, involved in Columbia University's Gaza ceasefire protests, awaits further legal proceedings. The case raises debates on free speech and legal grounds for deportation amidst national security concerns.
title: Why is US trying to deport green-card holder Khalil? Five questions answered

description: US President Donald Trump has voiced support for Elon Musk, praising his contributions to the nation amid claims that 'Radical Left Lunatics' are boycotting Tesla to harm Musk. Trump announced plans to buy a Tesla to show solidarity with Musk, who has been appointed by Trump to head the Department of government efficiency. Critics dub Musk as the unofficial 'Co-President.'
title: 'Will buy a new one tomorrow': Trump defends Musk after Tesla shares take a hit

description: Apple has begun hiring for four new retail stores in Delhi NCR, Mumbai, Bengaluru, and Pune as part of its physical expansion in India. The success of Apple's first two Indian stores and the record iPhone sales underscore the growing importance of the Indian market for the company.
title: Apple Store ‘leader’ John Taffe announces India hiring plans: We're excited to …

description: Former Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte was arrested at Manila's airport upon his return from Hong Kong, following ICC directives for an investigation into his aggressive anti-drug campaign. The ICC is examining potential crimes against humanity during Duterte's tenure as mayor of Davao and president.
title: Ex-Philippine president Duterte arrested for 'crimes against humanity'

description: The PCB faced criticism from former players for its absence during the Champions Trophy final closing ceremony, where India defeated New Zealand. Despite the presence of PCB officials at the venue, protocol dictated only the heads of cricket boards were allowed on stage, leaving Pakistan unrepresented. ICC have now issued a statement after reports of PCB lodging an official protest.
title: ICC issues statement on PCB official's absence at Champions Trophy final
MEA cautions against job fraud after repatriating 283 Indians from Myanmar

description: The Sports Ministry has lifted the suspension of the Wrestling Federation of India (WFI) and restored its recognition. WFI president Sanjay Singh now has full control. The ministry issued directions for balanced decision-making and the adherence to selection and governance rules. All changes made during the suspension must be reverted within 4 weeks.
title: Sports Ministry lifts suspension of Indian wrestling federation

description: Several standout players from the ICC Champions Trophy caught the attention of IPL franchise scouts and owners with their exceptional performances. Cricketers like Ben Duckett, Tom Latham, and Matt Henry, who went unsold in the mega auction last November, now appear as attractive prospects for IPL 2025 replacement signings.
title: Tide may turn for IPL rejects who lit up Champions Trophy

description: India faced a potential setback in the Champions Trophy with Jasprit Bumrah's absence but turned to mystery spinner Varun Chakravarthy. Varun delivered outstanding performances, taking five wickets against New Zealand and crucial strikes in knockout matches, helping India win the title. His unique bowling and mental toughness earned praise and made him a key player.
title: How Varun Chakravarthy evolved to become India’s X-factor

description: India won the ICC Champions Trophy 2025, beating New Zealand in the final. Amid speculation about their retirement, Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli dismissed rumors, with Rohit stating they had no plans to retire from ODIs. Sharma's match-winning 76 runs played a key role in the final. Rohit played a crucial role in the final, scoring a match-winning 76 against New Zealand.
title: 'Hum koi retire nahi ho rahe hain': Rohit, Virat's stump mic chat
'Should be rectified: RSS leader revives India vs Bharat row

description: Elon Musk targeted USAID, highlighting financial waste and corruption, particularly in NGO funding. His team pushed for transparency and reforms in USAID and the Treasury, with Marco Rubio confirming major implementations of their suggestions. Critics argue about the legality of the cuts and potential risks to essential aid programs.
title: 'Tremendous amount of money being sent ... ': Musk reveals why DOGE targeted USAID

description: US National Intelligence Director Tulsi Gabbard will visit the Indo-Pacific region, including India, to build strong relationships and open communication lines. This marks the first visit by a top White House official to India under the Trump administration, following PM Modi's US visit, where he met Gabbard and discussed enhancing bilateral intelligence cooperation.
title: US Intel chief Tulsi Gabbard to visit India during her Indo-Pacific trip

description: A gold-smuggling racket involving Kannada actor Ranya Rao, daughter of a senior IPS officer, has prompted the arrest of her friend Tarun K Raju. This has led to a political uproar and a demand for a state government probe into the misuse of police protocol services at the airport.
title: Who is Tarun Raju? Businessman's role being probed in Ranya Rao gold smuggling case

description: India's success in the Champions Trophy, played entirely in Dubai, stirred debate regarding an unfair advantage. However, Wasim Akram dismissed these concerns, asserting India's dominance in global tournaments. India claimed the Champions Trophy by defeating New Zealand, marking their second ICC title in nine months, remaining unbeaten throughout both tournaments, showcasing their depth and leadership.
title: 'Had India played in Pakistan, they ... ': Wasim Akram on venue controversy

description: Pope Francis's condition has improved, and doctors no longer fear for his life, though he is expected to remain hospitalized for further treatment. The Vatican confirmed the 88-year-old pontiff's health is stable, and he has been responsive to treatments, including physical and respiratory therapy.
title: Pope Francis's condition improves, no imminent danger to life, says Vatican

description: Somil Mehta from Mirae Asset Sharekhan recommends buying HUL and SBI Card stocks today. HUL shows a positive trend with a target of Rs 2420, while SBI Card is anticipated to break out upwards with a target of Rs 940. Consult a financial advisor before investing.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for March 11

description: Gautam Gambhir and Rohit Sharma returned to India with the team after their Champions Trophy victory in Dubai. Gambhir landed in Delhi, while Rohit arrived in Mumbai. The team's return was subdued as players prepare for the IPL 2025 season, commencing on March 22. Rohit reached Mumbai around 8 PM, accompanied by his wife, who had been in Dubai supporting him during the final.
title: 'India Cha Raja!' Rohit Sharma gets thunderous welcome in Mumbai

description: LeBron James was caught on camera expressing frustration over comments made by Stephen A. Smith regarding his son, Bronny. The incident highlights the emotional stress faced by athletes and their families. Smith addressed the issue, understanding James's reaction as a father. The hot mic moment revealed the raw emotions behind James's public statements.
title: LeBron James caught ranting to Richard Jefferson about Stephen Smith

description: The Indian government has clarified that no commitments were made to the US on reducing tariffs, despite Donald Trump's claims. Commerce Secretary Sunil Barthwal informed a parliamentary panel that India and the US are working towards a mutually beneficial trade agreement, addressing long-term cooperation over immediate tariff adjustments. He assured lawmakers that India's interests would be protected in the negotiations.
title: No commitment to US on tariffs: Govt to Parlimantary panel

description: Rohit Sharma led India to a historic ICC Champions Trophy 2025 victory, securing their second ICC trophy in nine months with a thrilling win over New Zealand. He ended retirement speculations, affirming his intention to continue in the ODI format, leaving fans with an iconic celebration. Their previous triumph came in June 2024 when they defeated South Africa in the T20 World Cup final in Barbados.
title: Rohit Sharma's perfect 'stump toss' stuns Dubai after Champions Trophy win

description: US stocks experienced a significant decline on Monday, driven by ongoing tariff disputes and the potential for a federal government shutdown. Key factors include high stock valuations, economic uncertainty, and disappointing corporate earnings. Technology stocks, like Tesla, faced severe losses. Investors are keeping a close watch on inflation reports, interest rate policies, and government actions to stabilize the economy.
title: Trump trade war: US stock market loses $4 trillion in value

description: Sun Pharma, India's largest pharmaceutical company, is set to acquire Checkpoint Therapeutics for $355 million. This strategic acquisition will enhance Sun Pharma's specialty portfolio, including UNLOXCYT, an FDA-approved treatment for advanced skin cancer, expanding its global presence in oncology treatments.
title: Sun Pharma to acquire US oncology company for over Rs 3,000 crore

description: Sheryl Sandberg allegedly spent $13,000 on lingerie for herself and her assistant, and invited the assistant to her bed on a private jet, as per a new memoir. A Meta spokesperson has dismissed these allegations, asserting they are outdated and baseless.
title: Facebook on ex-employee's $13K lingerie claim: She was fired 8 years ago

description: Air India urged passengers to use lavatories for their intended purposes after a flight from Chicago to Delhi diverted back due to clogged toilets. Items like polythene bags, rags, and clothes were found in lavatory plumbing. The airline emphasized passenger safety and provided immediate assistance, including hotel accommodations and alternative flight options.
title: As clothes, plastic bags clog loos, AI issues an unusual appeal to flyers

description: A 30-year-old chef from a five-star hotel in Nagpur was arrested for flashing women on Wardha Road, sparking public outrage after a video of the incident went viral. The chef, who frequently filmed vulgar acts, was apprehended due to the footage captured by a college student. His phone contained explicit videos, including many filmed within his house.
title: Chef of Nagpur 5-star arrested for flashing women on road

description: Tamil Nadu chief minister M K Stalin condemned Union education minister Dharmendra Pradhan's remarks calling DMK MPs uncivilised. DMK MP Kanimozhi also criticized Pradhan for his comments. Pradhan's remarks led to DMK cadres protesting across Tamil Nadu, demanding an apology from the minister. Pradhan defended his stance on the National Education Policy, while BJP MPs supported the promotion of Sanskrit.
title: Dharmendra Pradhan’s ‘uncivilised MPs’ remark draws Stalin’s fire

description: DMK filed a privilege notice in Lok Sabha against Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan, accusing him of making defamatory remarks about Tamil Nadu during a discussion over the Samagra Shiksha Scheme. The notice claimed that Pradhan falsely stated TN's stance on a MoU with the Centre, thereby misleading the House and tarnishing the state's image.
title: DMK slaps privilege notice on education minister

description: Ukraine surpassed India as the world's top arms importer in 2020-24, with its imports rising significantly due to its war with Russia. India's arms imports, driven by tensions with China and Pakistan, accounted for 8.3% of global imports. India's imports from Russia decreased, while imports from France and Israel increased.
title: Dogs of war: Russian rumble makes Ukraine top arms buyer
Govt’s plan for festival rush: 80 backup trains
‘Many duplicate EPICs issued from 2008-2013'

description: Giani Kuldeep Singh Gargaj's coronation as jathedar of Takht Kesgarh Sahib and Akal Takht was marked by a notable absence of traditional rituals and high-ranking community members. Key Sikh organizations were also not present. Former Jathedar Bhai Ranjit Singh criticized the lack of reverence, while Panthic Talmel Sangathan announced protests against SGPC members who supported the decision.
title: Muted ceremony marks Giani Kuldeep’s jathedar installation

description: Leader of the House J P Nadda expressed the government's readiness to discuss any issue but criticized the opposition for attempting to disrupt proceedings through Rule 267. He condemned their walkout and reassured that there will be opportunities for discussions during the Union Budget debates over the next 10 days.
title: Opposition demands discussion on 'voter list discrepancies'

description: Justice Joymalya Bagchi of Calcutta High Court has been appointed to the Supreme Court by the President. He is scheduled to become the Chief Justice of India on May 26, 2031. Justice Bagchi is the second judge from Calcutta HC to rise to the top post in 40 years after Justice Altamas Kabir.
title: President appoints Justice Bagchi to Supreme Court

description: Punjab BJP media in-charge Vineet Joshi accused AAP of influencing young voters through exam questions highlighting AAP policies. AAP rebutted the allegation, calling it baseless and accused BJP of creating controversy. Joshi cited a Class XII political science question from March 4, while AAP stated that such questions are typical in political science exams.
title: Punjab boards exam paper has posers on AAP, sparks row
Rape charge against Maharashtra education baron’s kin

description: Rohit Sharma led India to a historic ICC Champions Trophy 2025 victory, securing their second ICC trophy in nine months with a thrilling win over New Zealand. He ended retirement speculations, affirming his intention to continue in the ODI format, leaving fans with an iconic celebration. Their previous triumph came in June 2024 when they defeated South Africa in the T20 World Cup final in Barbados.
title: Rohit Sharma's perfect 'stump toss' stuns Dubai after Champions Trophy win
‘Sangam water was safe’: Govt cites new report

description: The Swadeshi Jagran Manch (SJM) urged the Indian government to protect farmers and small businesses during bilateral trade negotiations, particularly with the US. They emphasized focusing on bilateral trade deals over multilateral agreements. SJM criticized President Trump for his stance on India's tariffs and highlighted the need for national interests to be maintained.
title: Shield farmers, small biz in US trade deals: RSS affiliate

description: The Modi government and the DMK clashed in the resumed Budget session over the three-language policy and the NEP MoU. Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan accused DMK of reversing their stance under pressure, leading to protests. DMK's Kanimozhi alleged diversion of TN funds and filed a privilege motion against Pradhan for misleading and indecent remarks.
title: Uproar in Parliament over NEP as Pradhan, DMK lock horns
